0.0.1 Background

Exploration of discard estimates from calendar year module developed for QM and SBRM species

0.0.2 Steps

  1. pull all merged trips from CAMS_OBS_CATCH

  2. Set stratification variables for all trips

# FULL Stratification variables

stratvars = c('SPECIES_STOCK'
              ,'CAMS_GEAR_GROUP'
                            , 'MESHGROUP'
                          , 'TRIPCATEGORY'
                          , 'ACCESSAREA')
- SPECIES_STOCK is taken from CAMS support table `MAPS.CAMS_STATAREA_STOCK`
- CAMS_GEAR_GROUP is derived from a support table (`MAPS.CAMS_GEARCODE_STRATA`)
- MESHGROUP is hardcoded for all trips according to decisions made by the mesh subgroup (see summary when available)
- SECTID comes from a CAMS matching table (`MAPS.MATCH_MULT_SECTID`)
  1. Run discaRd
    • there are sub-passes for year t and year t-1
# Assumed Stratification variables

stratvars = c('SPECIES_STOCK'
              , 'CAMS_GEAR_GROUP')

  1. The discaRd functions allow for an assumed rate to be calculated. This assumed rate is realtive to the stratification used in the functions. Here, the stratification is coarsened to SPECIES_STOCK and CAMS_GEAR_GROUP

  2. A transition rate is calculated between year t and year t-1. This rate determines how much, if any, information is used from previous years.

  3. Rates and DISCARD_SOURCE (in parentheses) are assigned for each trip according to:
    1. in season rate; >= 5 trips in Full Stratification
    1. Transition in season rate; < 5 trips in Full Stratification, year t, AND >= 5 trips in year t-1
    1. Assumed rate. This is the rate when there were <5 trips in season and <5 in previous season.
    1. Observed values used from obserevd trips; discard rate is NOT USED.

  1. CV calculations are available for (I) and (T). Obtaining a CV estimate for (A) would require a second pass of discaRd functions.

  2. Discard pounds per trip are calculated according to

    mutate(DISC_MORT_RATIO = coalesce(DISC_MORT_RATIO, 1)) %>%
    mutate(DISCARD = case_when(!is.na(LINK1) ~ DISC_MORT_RATIO*OBS_DISCARD
                                                         , is.na(LINK1) ~ DISC_MORT_RATIO*COAL_RATE*LIVE_POUNDS)
                 
            # COAL_RATE is the final discard rate used. It is 'coalesced' from the (I), (A) and (B) rates

By assigning SPECIES_STOCK as a stratification variable, the computation time is reduced. Each subtrip may only occur in a single statistical area so it should never cross stock boundaries.

Once the full table (CAMS_OBS_CATCH) is loaded, each species takes ~X seconds to process on the server.

Output tables are produced for each species. These can easily be recombined. Preliminary species tables have been shared on MAPS and CAMS_GARFO.

    MAPS.CAMS_DISCARD_EXAMPLE_CY_BLACKSEABASS_19
    CAMS_GARFO.CAMS_DISCARD_EXAMPLE_CY_BLACKSEABASS_19
    
    MAPS.CAMS_DISCARD_EXAMPLE_CY_BLUEFISH_19
    CAMS_GARFO.CAMS_DISCARD_EXAMPLE_CY_BLUEFISH_19
    
    MAPS.CAMS_DISCARD_EXAMPLE_CY_BUTTERFISH_19
    CAMS_GARFO.CAMS_DISCARD_EXAMPLE_CY_BUTTERFISH_19
    
    MAPS.CAMS_DISCARD_EXAMPLE_CY_LONGFINSQUID_19
    CAMS_GARFO.CAMS_DISCARD_EXAMPLE_CY_LONGFINSQUID_19
    
    MAPS.CAMS_DISCARD_EXAMPLE_CY_SHORTFINSQUID_19

0.0.3 Diagnostic Plots/Tables

2019 Federal Discard Totals by Source

Highest discrepancies for total discards with CAMS vs.QM ACL 2019 are with Butterfish, Mackerel and Black Sea Bass.

2019 CAMS State Discard Totals

Since discards from state trips were not estimated in 2019 QM ACL we will need to compare these with estimates from the stock assessments. Are lower than expected (except for bluefish).

2019 KALL Totals by Method and Source

Kall is higher for CAMS but due to differences in what species are included in landings (e.g., no clams in DMIS).

Histogram of iscard Rates by Species, Strata and Discard Source

Total Discard Estimates by Species, Stock and Discard Source

Not suprisingly, total discards at the end of the year come from strata with an in season rate.
